name babel-hebrew
category Package
revision 77914
shortdesc Babel support for Hebrew
longdesc The package provides the language definition file for support
longdesc of Hebrew in babel. Macros to control the use of text direction
longdesc control of TeX--XeT and e-TeX are provided (and may be used
longdesc elsewhere). Some shortcuts are defined, as well as translations
longdesc to Hebrew of standard "LaTeX names". For questions, bug
longdesc reports, or support, please open an issue in the repository.
longdesc Note: the package is in maintenance mode. Bugs will be fixed,
longdesc but no new features will be added. The .ldf file is only
longdesc compatible with pdfLaTeX or LaTeX. Even then, for documents
longdesc containing more than a short text in Hebrew, it is strongly
longdesc recommended to use LuaTeX (with babel's .ini file or
longdesc polyglossia). For short texts with pdfTeX, use the .ini file.
longdesc Consult the documentation of babel for better settings for
longdesc Hebrew.
