name microtype
category Package
revision 78228
shortdesc Subliminal refinements towards typographical perfection
longdesc The package provides a LaTeX interface to the micro-typographic
longdesc extensions that were introduced by pdfTeX and have since also
longdesc propagated to XeTeX and LuaTeX: most prominently, character
longdesc protrusion and font expansion, furthermore the adjustment of
longdesc interword spacing and additional kerning, as well as
longdesc hyphenatable letterspacing (tracking) and the possibility to
longdesc disable all or selected ligatures. These features may be
longdesc applied to customisable sets of fonts, and all
longdesc micro-typographic aspects of the fonts can be configured in a
longdesc straight-forward and flexible way. Settings for various fonts
longdesc are provided. Note that character protrusion requires pdfTeX,
longdesc LuaTeX, or XeTeX. Font expansion works with pdfTeX or LuaTeX.
longdesc The package will by default enable protrusion and expansion if
longdesc they can safely be assumed to work. Disabling ligatures
longdesc requires pdfTeX or LuaTeX, while the adjustment of interword
longdesc spacing and of kerning only works with pdfTeX. Letterspacing is
longdesc available with pdfTeX, LuaTeX or XeTeX. The alternative package
longdesc 'letterspace', which also works with plain TeX, provides the
longdesc user commands for letterspacing only, omitting support for all
longdesc other extensions.
depend etoolbox
