name url
category Package
revision 77682
shortdesc Verbatim with URL-sensitive line breaks
longdesc The command \url is a form of verbatim command that allows
longdesc linebreaks at certain characters or combinations of characters,
longdesc accepts reconfiguration, and can usually be used in the
longdesc argument to another command. (The \urldef command provides
longdesc robust commands that serve in cases when \url doesn't work in
longdesc an argument.) The command is intended for email addresses,
longdesc hypertext links, directories/paths, etc., which normally have
longdesc no spaces, so by default the package ignores spaces in its
longdesc argument. However, a package option "allows spaces", which is
longdesc useful for operating systems where spaces are a common part of
longdesc file names.
containersize 5516
containerchecksum 4d036b664abd4917c9237aaa84bd5f93baa5589fda698543ac31fe18ab686ec25926a127733435a0cb5f4230d0d3be05b392c0395eb57991e3e9f0b93fe4a35a
